explanation (o3):
 The annotated query selects the city of the single business with the highest review_count in the entire Business table:
  SELECT city FROM Business ORDER BY review_count DESC LIMIT 1
It never restricts the search to the two cities mentioned (Scottsdale and Anthem) and does not compare their respective maxima. Hence it does not answer the question, which explicitly asks to decide between Scottsdale and Anthem based on which city’s businesses obtain the larger MAX(review_count).

A correct approach would
1) keep only rows whose city is either Scottsdale or Anthem;
2) convert the textual `review_count` to an integer;
3) aggregate with MAX(review_count) per city;
4) pick the city with the larger value (or both if they tie).

